        {
          "type": "assistant",
          "text": "There's your answer — and it completely changes the picture.\n\n**No, it's not a \"version of Cursor\" limitation at all.** Cursor's per-workspace DBs store an `allComposers` list that explicitly maps every conversation ID to its workspace, regardless of type. 28 of the 64 pure chat conversations are resolved this way. The remaining 36 are unresolvable because their workspace DB has been **deleted** by Cursor (it prunes old workspace storage when those folders are closed long enough).\n\nSo the real breakdown:\n\n| Group | Count | Why |\n|---|---|---|\n| Workspace identified via `allComposers` | 28 | Workspace DB still exists |\n| Truly unresolvable | 36 | Workspace DB was deleted by Cursor |\n\nThis means the **correct fix** isn't adding tiers to `get_conversation_workspace_root` — it's building a `composerId → workspace path` map upfront from all per-workspace DBs before running `collect_context_conversations`. That map covers all conversation types (chat, agent, read-only) and is version-independent. The `messageRequestContext` fallback only matters for conversations whose workspace DB no longer exists.\n\nThe implementation would be:\n\n```rust\n// Before the loop in collect_context_conversations:\n// 1. Scan ~/Library/Application Support/Cursor/User/workspaceStorage/*/state.vscdb\n// 2. For each, read ItemTable[\"composer.composerData\"] → allComposers → composerId list\n// 3. Read workspace.json in same dir → folder path\n// 4. Build HashMap<composerId, workspace_path>\n// 5. Use this map as primary lookup; messageRequestContext as fallback\n```\n\nThe 36 deleted-workspace conversations are genuinely unresolvable — excluding them when workspace can't be determined is the right call.",
