        {
          "type": "assistant",
          "text": "## Problem Summary\n\n### The Bug\n`collect_context_conversations` in `post_commit.rs` (lines 761–894) pulls in Cursor conversations from **other workspaces** into the authorship log. The specific conversation seen in the debug log was from the `evalhub` project (CPEN-491) appearing in the `git-ai` repo's authorship log.\n\n### Root Cause\nThe function scans **all** `composerData:*` entries from Cursor's **global** SQLite DB (`~/Library/Application Support/Cursor/User/globalStorage/state.vscdb`) — every conversation from every workspace ever opened. For each conversation it calls `CursorPreset::get_conversation_workspace_root` to filter by workspace, but this function returns `None` for the majority of conversations, and when it does, the code **includes the conversation unconditionally** as a \"safe fallback\":\n\n```rust\n// post_commit.rs lines 837–860\nif let Some(conv_workspace) =\n    CursorPreset::get_conversation_workspace_root(&db_path, &conversation_id)\n{\n    // filter: skip if wrong workspace\n    if canonical_conv != canonical_repo { continue; }\n}\n// if None → falls through, conversation is included regardless of workspace\n```\n\n`get_conversation_workspace_root` (lines 1933–1964 in `agent_presets.rs`) returns `None` when no `messageRequestContext:<id>:<bubble_id>` rows exist in the global DB (excluding `WARM_SUBMIT`). These rows are only written for a subset of conversations — in practice, only ~95 of 317 total conversations in the DB have them.\n\n### What Was Investigated\nBy querying the actual Cursor SQLite databases:\n\n**Global DB** (`globalStorage/state.vscdb` — `cursorDiskKV` table):\n- 317 total conversations (`composerData:*` keys)\n- Only 95 have `messageRequestContext` rows → workspace detectable by current code\n- 222 have no `messageRequestContext` rows → workspace unknown, all included by fallback\n- Of those 222: some are older Cursor agent conversations, some are chat-mode\n\n**Per-workspace DBs** (`workspaceStorage/<hash>/state.vscdb` — `ItemTable`):\n- Every workspace-specific DB has a `composer.composerData` key containing `allComposers`: an **explicit list of every conversation ID created in that workspace**\n- The workspace path itself is in `workspace.json` in the same directory (e.g. `file:///Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai`)\n- 24 per-workspace DBs exist, providing 232 composerId→workspace mappings total\n- This covers all conversation types: agent, chat, read-only — completely version-independent\n- Checking the 64 \"pure chat with no file mentions\" conversations: 28 are resolvable via `allComposers`, 36 are not (their workspace DBs were deleted by Cursor's cleanup)\n\n**Other signals investigated and ruled out:**\n- `originalFileStates` in `composerData`: only populated when files are **edited**, not read\n- `messageRequestContext:WARM_SUBMIT` rows: stored as `null` value, useless\n- `context.mentions.fileSelections`: only present when user explicitly @-mentions files\n- Pure chat conversations: zero `messageRequestContext` rows of any kind — not a Cursor version issue, just no rows are written for them\n\n### Proposed Solution\n\n**Primary fix:** Build a `composerId → workspace_path` map from per-workspace DBs **before** the conversation loop in `collect_context_conversations`, then use it as the primary workspace lookup. Change the fallback from \"include if unknown\" to \"exclude if unknown.\"\n\n```rust\n// 1. Scan ~/Library/Application Support/Cursor/User/workspaceStorage/*/state.vscdb\n// 2. For each: read ItemTable[\"composer.composerData\"] → allComposers → composerId list\n//             read workspace.json in same dir → folder URI → strip \"file://\" → path\n// 3. Build HashMap<String, PathBuf>  (composerId → workspace path)\n//\n// 4. In the filter block, look up map first, fall back to messageRequestContext,\n//    and if still None → `continue` (exclude), not include\n```\n\nThe lookup priority should be:\n1. Per-workspace `allComposers` map (covers all conversation types, version-independent)\n2. `messageRequestContext` rows (fallback for conversations whose workspace DB was deleted)\n3. `None` → **exclude** (not include — reversal of current behavior)\n\nThe new `get_conversation_workspace_root` (or a new helper) would need a path to the workspace storage directory. On macOS this is `~/Library/Application Support/Cursor/User/workspaceStorage`. The existing `cursor_global_database_path()` pattern (respecting a `GIT_AI_CURSOR_GLOBAL_DB_PATH` env var) should be extended with a similar `cursor_workspace_storage_path()` helper for testability.",
